    <ul style="color: White; text-align: left">
        <li class="style7">There will be three rounds.</li>
        <li class="style7">First round will be an elimination round. This round is to judge the imagination power of teams. The teams have to prepare an abstract based on the given problem statement.</li>
        <li class="style7">The abstract must contain feasible design of the mechanism with proper specifications of the vehicles.</li>
        <li class="style7">On the basis of abstract 10 teams will be selected for next round.</li>
        <li class="style7">Second round comprises of interview round. In this round teams have to prepare proper charts and design to explain the mechanism and working of vehicles. On the basis of designs there will be an interview by the faculty.</li>
        <li class="style7">After the second round three teams will be selected for the final round.</li>
        <li class="style7">In this round teams have to design the vehicle according to the design presented using junk.</li>
        <li class="style7">The teams will be given access to workshops for two days.</li>
        <li class="style7">A team must comprise of 4-6 members.</li>
        <li class="style7">Each team must formulate their own ideas and designs. Any form of plagiarism will lead to disqualification.</li>
        <li class="style7">No extra time will be given to any team under any circumstances.</li>
        <li class="style7">Judges' decision shall be final and binding to all. </li>
        <li class="style7">The team must adhere to the spirit of healthy competition. Organizers reserve the right to disqualify any team found to indulge in misbehaviour.</li>
        <li class="style7">Organizers reserve the right to change any number of rules and the teams must abide to it.</li>
    </ul>
    
